<H3> <TI>   Air Force Chief Makes `Mystery' Visit to Amman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Air Force Chief Makes `Mystery' Visit to Amman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0604084094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 5 Apr 94 p4 </F>
<F P=103> PM0604084094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Iraqi Air Force Commander on Mystery </F>
Visit to Jordan"] 
  [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Informed Jordanian 
sources have revealed that Iraqi Air Force Commander Staff 
Lieutenant General Muzahim Sa'b al-Hasan al-Tikriti is now in 
Amman. The sources declined to give the date of the Iraqi 
military commander's arrival in Amman or the nature of his 
mission there. 
  The sources told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that the Iraqi military 
commander was staying at the Forte Grand Hotel. There was a 
fire on one floor of that hotel yesterday morning in which two 
Italian tourists were killed and 12 persons, including four 
Iraqis, were burned or suffered from smoke inhalation. 

</TEXT>

