<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation Meets Assembly Speaker </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation Meets Assembly Speaker </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0304132594 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1220 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0304132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 3 Apr (INA)--National Assembly Speaker 
Sa'di Mahdi Salih today received a delegation from the Jordanian 
House of Representatives led by Deputy House Speaker 'Abd Musa 
al-Nahar. 
  During the meeting, they reviewed Iraqi-Jordanian 
parliamentary ties and means of promoting them in the interest 
of the two fraternal countries. They also reviewed Arab and 
international developments in light of the continuation of the 
U.S.-Zionist conspiracy spearheaded by the United States and its 
partners, which is targeting Iraq and its unity. 
  The meeting was attended by the deputy speaker of the 
National Assembly and several chairmen of the Assembly's 
permanent committees. 

</TEXT>

