<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tariq 'Aziz Receives Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tariq 'Aziz Receives Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0504150194 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1320 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0504150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 5 Apr (INA)--Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 
'Aziz today received a delegation from the Jordanian House of 
Representatives headed by Deputy House Speaker 'Abd Musa 
al-Nahar. 
  The deputy prime minister explained in detail the human 
suffering and the [word indistinct] effect of the unfair 
embargo, which certain tyrannical and domineering parties at the 
UN Security Council seek to perpetuate, despite the fact that 
Iraq has fulfilled its commitments, which obliges the UN 
Security Council to lift the embargo clamped on Iraq in 
fulfillment of its reciprocal obligations. 
  Tariq 'Aziz commended Jordan's courageous stands in support 
of the Iraqi people, and urged parliamentarians as well as all 
organizations and well-intentioned people in the world to 
redouble their efforts to lift the unfair embargo clamped on the 
Iraqi people. 
  For his part, the deputy speaker of the Jordanian House of 
Representatives reiterated the Jordanian people's support for 
and solidarity with the fraternal Iraqis. He commended the 
Iraqis' steadfastness and firmness in their confrontation of the 
aggression and in their handling of the unfair embargo. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

