<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cuban Foreign Ministry Official Holds Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cuban Foreign Ministry Official Holds Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets Tariq 'Aziz </H4>

<F P=102> JN0204130994 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1150 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0204130994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 2 Apr (INA)--Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 
'Aziz received here today Nicolas Rodriguez, under secretary of 
the Cuban Ministry of Foreign Relations. 
  During the meeting, the talks addressed the friendly 
bilateral ties and the means of promoting them despite the 
embargoes clamped on both Iraq and Cuba. 
  The talks also addressed the imperialist U.S. policy, which 
seeks to perpetuate the iniquitous embargo clamped on Iraq, 
although Iraq has fulfilled all its commitments. The two 
officials also discussed the wicked embargo the United States is 
imposing on Cuba and its people to achieve tendentious political 
purposes. 
  The two sides asserted that adherence to independence is the 
best weapon to be used in confronting embargoes and conspiracies. 
  The meeting was attended by the Foreign Ministry under 
secretary and the Cuban charge d'affaires in Baghdad. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

