<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, Spanish Foreign Minister Discuss Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat, Spanish Foreign Minister Discuss Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0604170194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1615 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604170194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 Apr (MENA)--Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat today conferred with Spanish Foreign Minister Javier 
Solana shortly before Solana left Cairo. The meeting dealt with 
developments in the peace process and the position of Israel, 
which is placing obstacles before the process. The meeting also 
touched on the Spanish role in implementing Security Council 
Resolution 904. 
  The meeting was attended on the Palestinian side by PLO 
Executive Committee member Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh; Sa'id Kamal, 
Palestinian ambassador in Cairo; and Zuhdi al-Qidrah, the Fatah 
representative in Cairo. On the Spanish side, the meeting was 
attended by the Spanish ambassador in Cairo and some advisers. 

</TEXT>

