<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hebron Mayor Arrives in Cairo To Meet 'Arafat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hebron Mayor Arrives in Cairo To Meet 'Arafat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0604151894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1455 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 Apr (MENA)--Hebron Mayor Mustafa al-Natshah 
arrived in Cairo from Israel today on a four-day visit. 
  Upon his arrival, al-Natshah said the aim of his visit was 
to 
meet President Yasir 'Arafat to brief him on the situation in 
Hebron and to listen to his instructions for easing the 
suffering of the Hebron inhabitants, who were under curfew for 
30 days after which the city center was closed on the pretext of 
protecting Jewish families. 
  Al-Natshah explained that this closure inconvenienced 
120,000 
Palestinians. He said he would ask 'Arafat to explain this 
tragedy to President Mubarak so that he could try to help in 
this direction. 

</TEXT>

