<H3> <TI>   Government Forces Control 90 Percent of South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Forces Control 90 Percent of South </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0604210594 Nairobi KNA in English 1830 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0604210594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nairobi KNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 5 Apr (KNA/PANA) -- The Sudanese 
Government controls 90 percent of the territory in the south 
where a civil war has raged for some years, Mahdi Ibrahim, the 
director of political affairs in the Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs, has said. 
  Ibrahim disclosed this when he addressed a political forum 
in 
Omdurman Province. 
  He accused a rebel leader, John Garang, of fearing peace in 
the territory because he did not have any plans for its 
development. 

</TEXT>

