<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Education Minister Visits, Meets Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqi Education Minister Visits, Meets Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Received by Vice President </H4>

<F P=102> JN3103154294 Baghdad INA in English 1300 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3103154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, Mar. 31, INA -- Sudanese First 
Vice-President al-Zubayr Muhammad Salih expressed his people and 
leadership's appreciation for Iraq's national stance under the 
leadership of President Saddam Husayn. 
  During a meeting with Iraqi Minister of Higher Education and 
Scientific Research Dr. Humam 'Abd-al-Khaliq, General Salih said 
the people of Iraq who enjoyed high self-confidence and firm 
faith in Almighty God managed to reconstruct all that had been 
destroyed during the 30-state aggression and have confronted the 
blockade through depending on self-potentials. 
  The Sudanese vice-president stressed his country's adherence 
to its national and principled stances toward Iraq and the Arab 
nation. 
  The meeting, attended by Sudanese minister of education and 
scientific research, and the Iraqi ambassador in Khartoum, 
discussed means of expanding and developing cooperation and 
joint action between the two sisterly countries. 

</TEXT>

