<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Receives Saudi Agriculture Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Receives Saudi Agriculture Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704001194 Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network in Arabic 
2300 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704001194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This evening, in his office, Prime Minister Mohamed 
Karim Lambrani received Dr. 'Abd-al-Rahman Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz 
al-Shaykh, the Saudi minister of agriculture and water 
resources, in the presence of Finance Minister Mohamed Sagou, 
Abdelaziz Meziane Belfkih, minister of agriculture and agrarian 
reform, and Mohamed Seqat, governor of the Bank of Morocco. The 
discussion centered on the special relations existing between 
the two sister countries that are based on the close fraternal 
ties between the two monarchs, His Majesty King Fahd 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz Al Sa'ud, custodian of the two holy mosques, 
and His Majesty King Hassan II. 
  The prime minister and the Saudi minister of agriculture and 
water resources also reviewed bilateral cooperation in the field 
of agriculture and ways to bolster it, particularly in the 
projects linked to the national irrigation program in Morocco. 
The prime minister also highlighted the importance the Kingdom 
of Morocco attached to the agricultural sector, which is one of 
the priorities in the country's development policy in view of 
its vital role in the preservation of the country's economic and 
social balance. 

</TEXT>

