<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian-Israeli Committees Continue Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian-Israeli Committees Continue Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sha'th on Withdrawal, Police </H4>

<F P=102> JN0604125394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 0942 GMT 6 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0604125394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Dr. Nabil Sha'th, head of the Palestinian </F>
delegation, by Sha'ul Menashe in Cairo; date not given; from the 
"With the Midday Events" program -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Menashe] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, what is the current 
status of the negotiations? 
  [Sha'th] We are in the final days before the signing of an 
agreement and before the beginning of the withdrawal and entry 
of the Palestinian police force. In these final days, there is 
much and continuous work that should be done by all committees, 
and we are working seriously on this. We are aware that in 
these final days we should complete the work so that 
implementation can begin. In fact, implementation has actually 
begun. A withdrawal has begun and this is clear to all our 
people everywhere. Deportees are returning to shoulder specific 
responsibilities within the upcoming Palestinian administration. 
Preparations are being made for the entry of the vanguards of 
the Palestinian police. God willing, we will complete 
preparations for implementing this agreement as soon as possible. 
  [Menashe] Final question. Do you believe that the deployment 
of the Palestinian forces in the first stage should guarantee 
security for the Palestinian people in the territories after the 
departure of the Israeli forces? 
  [Sha'th] Undoubtedly. First, the Palestinian forces will 
enter before the withdrawal of the Israeli forces. The Israeli 
forces will then withdraw, and the Palestinian forces will 
become fully responsible for security. 
  [Menashe] When will the Palestinian forces be armed? 
  [Sha'th] The Palestinian forces will be armed upon their 
entry, but their security responsibility will begin when the 
Israeli forces withdraw. 
  [Menashe] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, thank you very much. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

