<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Hijacking of Sudanese Plane to Luxor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Hijacking of Sudanese Plane to Luxor </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Seeking Asylum </H4>

<F P=102> NC0604131594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1250 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Luxor, 6 Apr (MENA)--Mahjub Husayn Muhammad, the 
hijacker of the Sudanese airliner, has stated that he chose to 
seek political asylum in Egypt because it is a safe and dear 
country. He said that the political, economic, and social 
situation in Sudan is deteriorating. The hijacked Sudanese 
airliner landed at Luxor airport this morning and the hijacker 
surrendered to the Egyptian authorities. 

</TEXT>

