94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0704061194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Minister Shim'on Shetrit will propose that the 
government suspend the negotiations with the PLO until Yasir 
'Arafat condemns the terrorist attack in 'Afula. Shetrit 
expressed the belief that all the cabinet ministers will support 
his proposal. The minister said that not only has 'Arafat failed 
to condemn the terrorist attack of his own volition but also 
avoided replying to a question on the matter yesterday in Cairo. 
  Shetrit explained that by his actions, 'Arafat is giving 
cause to doubt the sincerity of his intention to fulfill his 
commitments to Israel. Shetrit said that Prime Minister Rabin 
and Foreign Minister Peres will find the appropriate time and 
place to comment on 'Arafat's behavior. 

