<H3> <TI>   Further Incidents in Territories Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Incidents in Territories Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0704055994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 7 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0704055994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An Israeli resident of the Qatif Bloc was stabbed 
and slightly wounded this morning by a terrorist near the 
Kissufim checkpoint in the Gaza Strip. He is currently being 
evacuated to a hospital in Beersheba. 
  Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that the Israeli came to 
the checkpoint to pick up workers. On his way back to the Qatif 
Bloc, he was stabbed in the chest and shoulder by one of the 
workers. The terrorist dropped the knife and fled. Other 
workers called soldiers from the checkpoint who found the 
wounded man in his car. The security forces have launched a 
manhunt after the assailant. 
  In another incident, an Israeli citizen was injured in 
Qalqilyah when his car was pelted with stones. He lost control 
of the vehicle, which overturned. The man sustained moderate 
injuries and was taken to a hospital in Kefar Sava. 
  The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] tightened the closure on the 
territories this morning and increased security at its 
checkpoints, especially in Samaria. Soldiers are conducting 
very thorough inspections and hardly any Samaria Arabs are being 
permitted to enter the Green Line. 

</TEXT>

