<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] A total closure will be imposed on the 
territories from 1700 [1400 GMT] this afternoon, following the 
recent spate of terrorist attacks. Our correspondent Shlomo Raz 
reports that from that hour onwards, Arabs from the territories 
will not be permitted to enter the Green Line. 
  This morning, the chief of staff said it is impossible to 
completely prevent terrorist attacks in retaliation for the 
Hebron massacre. He praised the soldiers at the Ashdod Junction 
for showing initiative by shooting and killing the terrorist. 
  The prime minister will convene the Ministerial Committee on 
Security Affairs for a special session tomorrow in order to 
discuss the deterioration in the security situation and decide 
on the necessary steps. 
  The leaders of the opposition factions are meeting at Likud 
headquarters in Tel Aviv this afternoon to discuss the 
situation. They will demand the establishment of a commission of 
inquiry into the wave of terrorist attacks and a halt to the 
negotiations with the PLO. Tzomet leader Refa'el Eytan called 
on the government to resign and call new elections. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

