<H3> <TI>   Sources Report `Jordanian Afghans' in Africa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sources Report `Jordanian Afghans' in Africa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0604143194 Amman AL-BILAD in Arabic 6 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> JN0604143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-BILAD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to well-informed sources, who spoke to 
AL-BILAD, the existence of "Jordanian Afghans," cannot be ruled 
out. But there are only a handful of them. They fled 
Afghanistan to Kenya among a group of other Arabs who have 
recently sought refuge in Africa. 
  Led by Ayman al-Zawahiri, an Egyptian medical doctor, this 
group is seeking entry into southern Sudan from Kenya. 
Al-Zawahiri has been to Nairobi a number of times in an effort 
to find a place for Arabs forced to leave Pakistan. Khartoum 
has balked at accepting them. 
  Over the past three months, there has been a mass exodus of 
"Arab Afghans" who have taken Pakistan's threats to expel them 
seriously. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

