<H3> <TI>   U.S. Envoy Denies Israel Guilty of Church Bombing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Envoy Denies Israel Guilty of Church Bombing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704065594 Beirut AL-SHIRA' in Arabic 4 Apr 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704065594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut AL-SHIRA' </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "First News" section] </F>
  [Text] Official sources with first-hand access to security 
matters say that the bomb planted in Sayyidat al-Najat Church 
was brought from Israel and assembled at a Lebanese Forces' 
center in Lebanon. 
  [A related item from the same "First News" section adds: 
"Ministerial quarters have expressed puzzlement over the 
insistence of U.S. Ambassador Mark Hambley in his private 
discussions that Israel had nothing to do with the bombing in 
Sayyidat al-Najat Church in Zuq Mikha'il, a position that 
conflicts with the evidence accumulated by the security organs 
and judiciary."] 

</TEXT>

