  [Text] Serb forces are only 5 km away from the 
Muslim-inhabited town of Gorazde. UN reports indicate that the 
Serb forces have advanced 10 km in the area, but UN officials 
still say that Gorazde is not facing a serious threat. 
  Meanwhile, the Islamic Republic of Iran has called for 
speedy 
action by the United Nations to prevent the fall of Gorazde and 
the massacre of its innocent inhabitants. In a letter to the 
United Nations, our country's foreign affairs minister has also 
made reference to the fact that Gorazde was earlier declared a 
safe area. The letter, furthermore, cautions against the 
occurrence of yet another tragedy in Bosnia. 
  The Islamic countries have also started a series of 
diplomatic initiatives in the United Nations with the aim of 
inducing the Security Council to pass a resolution to prevent 
the fall of Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

