<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   $800-Million Loan To Repay Italian Debts Received </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    $800-Million Loan To Repay Italian Debts Received </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704073094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0704073094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iran and Italy have signed a long-term financial 
agreement and have thus ended their differences in this field. 
The Central News Unit reports that on the basis of this 
financial agreement, which was signed by a delegation of the 
Central Bank of the Islamic Republic of Iran and Italian 
financial officials and the state Italian insurance organization 
(SACE), an $800-million credit has been placed at the disposal 
of the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  On the basis of this agreement, all debts by state and 
private companies and by Iranian importers to their Italian 
trade partners that have not been paid up until now will be paid 
by this credit. All the debts of 1373 [year beginning 21 March 
1994] that will mature within the coming months will also be 
paid by this credit. The credit covers all purchases that are 
covered by the Italian state insurance company (SACE). The 
credit is for a period of six years, comprising two years of a 
grace period and four years of repayment. 
  The Central Bank has previously signed similar financial 
agreements with Germany, Japan, Switzerland, Austria, and Poland. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

