<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Views Kashmir, Talbott Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Views Kashmir, Talbott Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0604144194 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0604144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has refuted press reports as totally 
baseless suggesting that the United States has proposed to 
Islamabad to freeze the Kashmir issue. A Foreign Office 
spokesman briefing newsmen in Islamabad today said Pakistan has 
received neither any paper nor any nonpaper on this subject. 
[sentence as heard] 
  To a question, the spokesman said Pakistan resents deeply 
the 
proliferation of false and defamatory statements from India 
alleging the involvement of Pakistan's Inter Service 
