<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bhutto Receives DPRK Deputy Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bhutto Receives DPRK Deputy Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0604163194 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0604163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The deputy prime minister of Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea, Mr. Hong Song-nam, paid a courtesy call on 
the prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, in Islamabad today. 
During the meeting, the prime minister hoped that the visit of 
the deputy prime minister of Korea would result in increased 
economic cooperation between the two countries. Mr. Hong 
Song-nam conveyed greetings and best wishes of the president of 
North Korea, Mr. Kim Il-song, for the prime minister which she 
fully reciprocated. 

</TEXT>

