<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Briefs French Foreign Minister Juppe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Briefs French Foreign Minister Juppe </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Discuss Kashmir Situation </H4>

<F P=102> BK0404140794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0404140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] France has opposed internationalizing the Kashmir 
issue by Pakistan. The visiting French foreign minister, Mr. 
Alain Juppe, assured his country's support to India's stand and 
hoped talks between India and Pakistan will resume soon to sort 
out the issue. The matter came up for detailed discussions at 
his meeting with the prime minister, Mr. Narasimha Rao; the 
external affairs minister, Mr. Dinesh Singh; and the home 
minister, Mr. S.B. Chavan. Mr. Rao briefed Mr. Juppe about 
Pakistan's support to terrorism on Indian soil and Islamabad's 
interference to undermine India's territorial integrity. The 
prime minister said India is open to bilateral discussions with 
Pakistan. 

</TEXT>

