<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six Soldiers, Seven Civilians Killed in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Six Soldiers, Seven Civilians Killed in Kashmir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0704022194 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0704022194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Six Indian soldiers were killed and seven civilians 
were martyred in clashes between the freedom fighters and Indian 
troops in various areas of the valley in occupied Kashmir. Four 
soldiers of the Indian paramilitary force were killed and one 
freedom fighter was martyred in a clash at (Rayar) in Badgam 
today. Biswajit Mandal, a military officer of the Border 
Security Force, was killed and four personnel were injured in 
Batamalu. A report says that an Indian soldier shot and killed 
his officer, Man Singh, at Nagrota camp. In Rafiabad, 24 people 
were arrested while 12 houses and shops were set ablaze in the 
Kangan area of Srinagar. Meanwhile, the All Party Hurriet 
Conference at a meeting in Srinagar reaffirmed its stand that 
the Kashmir issue can be resolved only when the Kashmiris are 
granted an opportunity to exercise their right to 
self-determination under UN auspices. The meeting, presided 
over by Mirwaiz Umar Farooq, rejected any attempt by India to 
initiate the so-called political process. 

</TEXT>

