<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    20 Killed in Intergang Warfare in Kashmir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0704110394 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0704110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Kashmir valley, 20 militants have been killed in 
inter-gang warfare during the last fortnight. The group clashes 
between different militant organizations have spread to almost 
every district of the valley. Yesterday, a self-styled district 
commander of the JKLF [Jammu and Kashmir Liberation Front] was 
killed by Hizbul Mojahedin at Chandpura in Srinagar. After the 
incident, thousands of people came out in the streets in 
Srinagar shouting slogans against the militants. Last week 
also, a procession was taken out in (Ashmukan) town by local 
residents to protest against the activities of the militant 
groups. 

