<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian-Israeli Committees Continue Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian-Israeli Committees Continue Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Agreement To Meet in Cairo 8 Apr </H4>

<F P=102> NC0704095394 Paris AFP in English 0939 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704095394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, April 7 (AFP) -- Israel and the PLO have 
agreed to meet again in Cairo on Friday [8 April] to try to 
finalize an accord on launching Palestinian autonomy, chief 
Palestinian negotiator Nabil Sha'th said Thursday. 
  Palestinian and Israeli officials reached the decision over 
the telephone on Thursday morning, Sha'th told AFP. The two 
sides had agreed to reconvene on Sunday after adjourning 
autonomy talks on Wednesday. 
  They will meet Friday on the Moslem traditional day of rest. 
  Sha'th had criticized Israeli negotiators for heading home 
to 
observe a Holocaust remembrance day on Thursday, and said it 
would be difficult now to finalize an accord on launching 
autonomy by an April 13 deadline. 
  Under the September accord the two signed in Washington, 
Israel was to have begun withdrawing its troops from Gaza and 
Jericho on December 13 and completed the move by April 13. 
  The first deadline was missed, but PLO chief Yasir 'Arafat 
insisted in Jordan on Wednesday that the withdrawal take place 
in a week's time. 

</TEXT>

