<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Brave' Hamas Attack at Israeli Bus Stop Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Brave' Hamas Attack at Israeli Bus Stop Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704055894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0345 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0704055894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary by News Research and Commentaries Group] </F>
  [Text] The brave and martyr-seeking attack by a Palestinian 
mujahid at a Zionist bus stop -- on the 40th day of the massacre 
of fasting worshipers in the al-Khalil mosque -- which resulted 
in the death of eight Zionists and the wounding of more than 50 
others, shows, first and foremost, that the era of the intifadah 
is different from the past. By undertaking responsibility for 
this operation, the Palestinian Islamic Resistance Movement 
Hamas stated that the car explosion at a Zionist bus stop in 
'Afula in the north of occupied Palestine is in answer to the 
massacre of the fasting Palestinian worshipers at the 
al-Ibrahimi shrine and in order to avenge their unjustly shed 
blood. 
  Political observers believe that this attack demonstrates 
the 
strength of the Palestinian Islamic movement in organizing and 
carrying out jihad operations. Yesterday's attack took place on 
the anniversary of the commencement of the intifadah and the 
Zionist forces were on full alert. The place where the 
operation took place was north of occupied Palestine, or, in 
other words, outside the West Bank and Gaza Strip, a place where 
carrying out operations is extremely difficult. The admission 
by the Zionist chief of staff that the Zionist regime's military 
forces will not be able to prevent such operations in the future 
proves this point even further. 
  Since its founding, the Zionist regime has unilaterally 
massacred and rendered homeless the people of Palestine and Arab 
countries that share borders with occupied Palestine. Because 
of the unequal military balance and extensive support by 
international powers for the usurping regime, the reaction by 
the people of Palestine and the world has not been strong enough 
to stop this inhuman process. However, now that the Muslim 
Palestinians have been armed with the spirit of jihad and 
martyrdom, the situation has completely changed. 
  Seven years ago, with the commencement of the intifadah and 
the persistent struggle against the Zionist regime, the 
Palestinians gave up the past beliefs of political leaders of 
Palestine in defending the rights of the Palestinian Muslims 
through international organizations. By relying on the 
Palestinian people and their Islamic belief, they set off on a 
path that has proven to be effective and, God willing, will lead 
to victory in the not very distant future. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

