<H3> <TI>   PLO Issues Statement of Condolences on 'Afula Events </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Issues Statement of Condolences on 'Afula Events </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704155494 Paris AFP in English 1526 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, April 7 (AFP)--The PLO expressed its 
condolences Thursday to the families of the seven Israelis 
killed when a teenage Palestinian militant rammed his 
explosive-packed car into a bus in the northern Israeli town of 
Afula. 
  An official PLO spokesman said in a statement to AFP: "The 
PLO presents its condolences to the families of the victims (of 
the attack)," which also left 45 wounded. 
  "The PLO hopes that all concerned parties will assume their 
responsibility to safeguard the peace process and achieve its 
aims, to ensure a just and equal solution between the 
Palestinian and Israeli peoples," the statement said. 
  The United States called on PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat 
Wednesday to condemn the Afula attack, carried out by a 
19-year-old member of the Islamic Resistance Movement HAMAS, 
which is opposed to the peace process. 

</TEXT>

