<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Says Incident Highlights Need for Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Says Incident Highlights Need for Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704171294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1620 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Apr (MENA)--The PLO has announced that the 
'Affula incident yesterday confirms the urgent need to achieve 
tangible progress to implement the interim agreement and to 
undertake practical measures to prove the seriousness of the 
peace process. 
  In a statement by an official Palestinian spokesman in Cairo 
today, the PLO expressed its grief over the incident, which left 
several Israeli civilians dead. 
  The organization noted that the series of actions that began 
with the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre in Hebron and subsequent 
massacres, most notably that in the Jabalyah refugee camp in the 
Gaza Strip, where Israeli military forces have killed PLO 
cadres, confirms the urgent need to establish peace. 
  The spokesman said the PLO extends its condolences to the 
families of the civilian victims and hopes that all the parties 
concerned will assume their responsibility of safeguarding the 
peace process and achieving its goals to ensure a just and 
balanced solution guaranteeing genuine coexistence between the 
Palestinian and Israeli peoples. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

