<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Adviser Notes Peres Request </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Adviser Notes Peres Request </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0804052294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2125 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0804052294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Apr (MENA)--Marwan Kanafani, Palestinian 
president Yasir 'Arafat's adviser, has expressed his surprise 
over Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres' statements, in 
which he asks the Palestinian president to personally condemn 
the 'Affula incident. 
  In a statement he made this evening, Kanafani said in answer 
to Peres' statements that it is very strange to hear such a 
request from the Israeli foreign minister--neither he nor 
Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin expressed any kind of 
regret or condemnation when the Israeli army and intelligence 
deliberately killed six prominent youths from Fatah recently in 
Jabalyah in the Gaza Strip. 
  The Palestinian official added that the contrary was true 
since the Israeli housing minister expressed his and the Israeli 
Government's appreciation for such terrorist acts when he 
emerged from the Israeli cabinet's weekly session to declare the 
cabinet's stance on the incident. 

</TEXT>

