<H4>    U.S. Envoy Given Message for Clinton </H4>

<F P=102> LD0704174794 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 7 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother President leader Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] 
received the charge d'affaires of the U.S. Embassy in Cairo this 
afternoon. During the meeting, Brother Abu-'Ammar entrusted the 
charge d'affaires with a verbal message for President Bill 
Clinton on the talks currently under way on the implementation 
of the declaration of principles agreement, signed in 
Washington, and the agreements signed in Cairo. The message 
also concerns the attempts and obstacles trumped up by the 
Israeli Government to enable it to avoid implementing the 
agreements, a matter which exposes the peace process to danger. 

</TEXT>

