  [Text] Cairo, 7 Apr (MENA)--Palestinian president Yasir 
'Arafat held a meeting this evening at his place of residence in 
the guest palace in Cairo with the troika ambassadors, who are 
from Greece, Germany, and Belgium. 
  The Palestinian president explained to the troika 
ambassadors 
about developments in the Middle East peace process, the 
obstacles Israel is placing in the way, and the Palestinian 
stance on the issues. 
  The meeting was attended by Acting Palestinian Ambassador 
Zuhdi al-Qidrah, the Fatah representative in Cairo. 
  The troika is made up of three members of the European Union 
[EU]: the country that is currently chairing the EU, the 
country that chaired it during the previous round, and the 
country that will chair it during the second half of this year. 

