Daily Report 
<DATE1>  5 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spanish Foreign Minister Arrives in Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spanish Foreign Minister Arrives in Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0504144194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1425 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0504144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 5 Apr (MENA) -- Spanish Foreign Minister 
Javier Solana arrived in Cairo today on an official two-day 
visit, during which he will head his country's delegation to the 
meeting of the Joint Higher Egyptian-Spanish Committee. 
Egyptian Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa will head the Egyptian side 
to the meeting, which will begin later today. Talks between the 
two sides began on the level of experts yesterday. 
  During the visit, the Spanish foreign minister will meet 
with 
Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid to 
discuss Arab-Spanish cooperation. He will also meet with a 
number of Palestinian officials to review the latest 
developments in the peace talks and the role that Spain and the 
European Community can play to promote these talks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

