<H3> <TI>   Confers With Arab League Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Confers With Arab League Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0604103694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0920 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604103694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 Apr (MENA)--Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid today met with Spanish Foreign Minister 
Javier Solana, who is currently visiting Egypt. After the 
meeting, Solana said that he and 'Abd-al-Majid discussed the 
latest developments in the peace process in the Middle East. He 
expressed his country's interest in the achievement of stability 
in the region. He noted that he reviewed the results of the 
seminar on cooperation in the Mediterranean which concluded 
recently in Cairo. They also discussed ways of strengthening 
ties and broadening cooperation between the Arab League and the 
European Union. Solana described his talks with 'Abd-al-Majid 
as friendly and candid. He said that he extended an invitation 
to Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid to visit Spain for further discussions and 
exchange of views on issues of common concern to both parties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

