<H3> <TI>   Ministerial Meeting Planned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministerial Meeting Planned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604172494 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1300 GMT 6 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604172494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, 6 April, Spanish Foreign Minister Javier 
Solana met Egyptian President Husni Mubarak, to whom he handed 
an invitation to visit Spain from King Juan Carlos. Solana is 
also due to meet PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat in Cairo. 
  Solana and Mubarak decided to hold an informal ministerial 
meeting of 10 Mediterranean countries next July in the city of 
Alexandria. 
  Today in Cairo, Solana also met Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid, the 
general secretary of the Arab League, with whom he discussed the 
Middle East peace process, the dialogue among Mediterranean 
people, and the situation in the Arab countries. 
  Regarding the meeting with 'Arafat, Solana has repeated at 
every opportunity during his trip to Egypt Spain's willingness 
to help toward a successful conclusion of the peace process. 
This is the main purpose of his meeting today with the 
Palestinian leader. 

</TEXT>

