<H3> <TI>   Leaves Cairo After One-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leaves Cairo After One-Day Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0604144494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1350 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 6 Apr (MENA)--Spanish Foreign Minister Javier 
Solana left Cairo today after a one-day visit during which he 
was received by President Husni Mubarak. He also chaired the 
annual meeting of the Joint Spanish-Egyptian Committee, which 
has been meeting annually since it was formed in 1988. 
  During the visit Solana signed one agreement on protecting 
investments and another on avoiding double taxation. 
  Ambassador Hasan al-'Ujayzi, chief of the Foreign Ministry's 
Protocol Department, saw him off at the airport. 

</TEXT>

