<H3> <TI>   AL-SHA'B Chief Editor, Reporter Interrogated, Released </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    AL-SHA'B Chief Editor, Reporter Interrogated, Released </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0404202094 Cairo MENA in English 2000 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0404202094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, April 4 (MENA)--Majdi Ahmad Husayn, chief 
editor of AL-SHA'B newspaper, organ of the opposition Labour 
Party, and 'Abd-al-Sattar Abu-Husayn, an editor in the same 
paper, were released by the prosecution after being interrogated 
in connection with a complaint filed against them by the head of 
the Heliopolis Company for Chemicals. 
  The paper had accused the company head of allowing relatives 
to submit tenders and using the company's potentials in the 
service of his family members in violation of the law. 
  The two journalists asserted that they have documents 
proving 
that and pledged to put them forward on Saturday. 

</TEXT>

