<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Three `Terrorists' Killed in Asyut Clash </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Three `Terrorists' Killed in Asyut Clash </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0404162594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1550 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0404162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Asyut, Upper Egypt, 4 Apr (MENA)--Three terrorists 
were killed today in a clash with security forces and citizens 
in Asyut. The clash took place on the al-Ma'abidah Island in 
Markaz Manfalut, Asyut Governorate. 
  Several citizens clashed with three people, strangers to the 
island, who had weapons hidden under their clothes. When the 
three noticed that the citizens were in pursuit, they opened 
fire on them. A crowd gathered and chased them, preventing their 
escape. One of the three terrorists was wounded [as received] 
in an exchange of fire with citizens carrying licensed weapons. 
The citizens apprehended the other two terrorists to hand them 
over to the security forces who arrived on the island. When the 
two realized the security forces were approaching, they tried to 
escape, prompting the policemen to shoot them. They died 
instantly. The terrorists were found in possession of an 
automatic rifle and a pistol. The pistol belonged to a 
noncommissioned police officer who was assassinated last year. 
The Manfalut prosecutor started an investigation into the 
incident. 

</TEXT>

