<H3> <TI>   Peace Talks Boycotted Until al-'Aqabah `Siege' Resolved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peace Talks Boycotted Until al-'Aqabah `Siege' Resolved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0704163794 Amman AL-RA'Y in Arabic 7 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0704163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-RA'Y </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Hague -- The environment committee of the 
multilateral Middle East peace negotiations met for one day of 
talks in the Hague today, Thursday. 
  Informed Foreign Ministry sources said Jordan did not send 
an 
official delegation to the session because we are still awaiting 
Washington's decision on the Port of al-'Aqabah blockade, 
anticipated this week. 
  Jordan, sources told AL-RA'Y, sent its ambassador in Rome 
Hasan Abu-Na'imah to the Hague meeting as an observer rather 
than participant. 

</TEXT>

