<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spanish Foreign Minister Solana Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spanish Foreign Minister Solana Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Solana Ends Visit, Departs </H4>

<F P=102> NC0704202094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704202094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Spanish delegation, led by Foreign Minister 
Javier Solana, ended its visit to Lebanon after the foreign 
minister and his Lebanese counterpart, Faris Buwayz, met with 
the president, prime minister, and speaker of the Chamber of 
Deputies. The accompanying delegation members also concluded 
their talks with Foreign Ministry officials. The outlines for 
agreements on Lebanese-Spanish cooperation in economics and 
culture were formulated. [passage omitted] 
  The Spanish delegation left Beirut Airport this afternoon 
after being seen off by Ambassador Zafir al-Hasan, the Spanish 
ambassador to Lebanon, several government and security 
officials, and Spanish Embassy staff members. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

