<F P=103> NC0704105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Al-Shati' refugee camp, Occupied Gaza Strip, April 7 
(AFP) -- Islamic Jihad claimed responsibility for shooting dead 
an Israeli and wounding four others on Wednesday [as received]. 
  "The Islamic Jihad movement mourns with dignity and pride 
our 
martyr 'Ali Talib al-'Ammawi, hero of the Ashdod crossing 
operation," the fundamentalist group said in a statement. 
  The family live in al-Shati' refugee camp on the edge of 
Gaza 
City and his father Muhammad told AFP the boy was 19 years old 
and in his last year at high school. 
  He said his son had supported the fundamentalist movement 
Islamic Jihad. 
  Al-'Ammawi stepped off a bus at the port city of Ashdod and 
opened fire on a group of Israelis with an Uzi sub-machinegun, 
police said. 

</TEXT>

