<H3> <TI>   Settler Leader Claims Area of Jericho Enclave Enlarged </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Settler Leader Claims Area of Jericho Enclave Enlarged </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0704051894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 7 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0704051894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] David Levi, the chairman of the Jordan Rift Valley 
Regional Council, says that according to an updated map he has 
seen, the boundaries of the Jericho autonomous enclave will be 
larger than what was recently agreed upon with the PLO. The 
town's boundaries have been expanded to include an area of 
several square kilometers to the south. The perimeters of the 
village of al-'Awja' have also been expanded almost up to the 
border fence. Levi told our correspondent Gil Litman that 
construction work on the Jericho bypass road has not yet begun. 

</TEXT>

