<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iran's Ruhani Meets Other Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iran's Ruhani Meets Other Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0704190594 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 7 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0704190594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sana' al-Imam from Damascus] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The Iranian parliamentary 
delegation led by Hojjat ol-Eslam Hasan Ruhani, Iranian deputy 
Majles speaker, held several meetings in Damascus with the 
pro-Iran Iraqi opposition factions, such as al- Da'wah Party and 
the Supreme Assembly of the Islamic Revolution. Ruhani was 
quoted as saying that those who depend on the United States to 
liberate Iraq will be disappointed because the United States 
wants to control Iraq. 
  Ruhani also held talks with the 10 Palestinian factions that 
oppose the Gaza-Jericho accord. He also held talks in Damascus 
with representatives of the Hizballah and the Islamic resistance 
in Lebanon. Following his meeting with those representatives, 
Ruhani stressed the importance of a united Islamic resistance 
stand, reiterating Iran's readiness to continue to support 
Islamic resistance against Israeli schemes. 
  In a statement to Monte Carlo, Palestinian sources denied 
any 
Iranian financial siege on Hizballah and the Islamic Jihad. 
They stressed that the delay in Iranian financial aid in 
October 1993 was caused by a financial crisis in the Bank of 
Iran. This was communicated to them by the Iranian leadership 
in a written letter. The Palestinian sources said this temporary 
delay completely ended by December 1993. 

</TEXT>

