<H3> <TI>   Khaddam, Hizballah Secretary Stress Continuation of Jihad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khaddam, Hizballah Secretary Stress Continuation of Jihad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704185894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0704185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Lebanese Hizballah delegation headed by Hasan 
Nasrallah, the party secretary general, held talks with Syrian 
Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam in Damascus last night. In 
a statement issued in Beirut, Hizballah said the delegation and 
the Syrian vice president discussed developments in the region 
and the ongoing and increasing Zionist acts of aggression 
against south Lebanon. The statement said the two sides 
stressed the need to continue jihad against the Zionist 
campaigns against south Lebanon. 

</TEXT>

