<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Reshuffle Believed Imminent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Reshuffle Believed Imminent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0604144894 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 6 Apr 94 p1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0604144894 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ghunaym Muhammad al-Mutayri: "Kuwaiti Cabinet </F>
Reshuffle To Include Oil and Interior Ministries"] 
  [Text] Kuwait -- There was an atmosphere of anticipation 
and expectation in Kuwait yesterday as the countdown began for 
the announcement of the names to be included in the new cabinet. 
There is all kinds of speculation in various circles with 
everyone expressing his own views as to who will be appointed 
and who will be dismissed, but the final decision rests with 
Prime Minister and Heir Apparent Shaykh Sa'd al-'Abdallah 
al-Salim al-Sabah who is still holding consultations on this 
matter. 
  AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT has learned from sources close to Shaykh 
Sa'd that the expected cabinet reshuffle will be ready within 
the next few days and may be announced Saturday. 
  The sources added that the cabinet reshuffle will cover the 
ministries of oil, interior, electricity, works, communications, 
and housing but will not affect the other main ministries such 
as the foreign, defense, and information ministries. 
  The sources also said that some new names have been tipped 
for important ministries. They include Shaykh Jabir 'Abdallah 
al-Jabir al-Sabah, the former cabinet affairs minister who held 
the post at the time of the occupation and liberation and who 
also held other posts such as governor of al-Ahmadi and governor 
of Hawalli. Other prominent names include al-Ahmadi Governor 
Shaykh Muhammad al-Khalid al-Sabah and former Defense Minister 
Shaykh Nawwaf al-Ahmad al-Sabah. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

