<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ummah Party Leader Reportedly `Rearrested' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ummah Party Leader Reportedly `Rearrested' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704142594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1335 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0704142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Apr (MENA)--The Sudanese Ummah Party has 
announced that the Sudanese security agencies rearrested 
al-Sadiq al-Mahdi, leader of the party and former prime 
minister, 24 hours after releasing him, without giving any 
reasons. 
  The party said in a statement in Cairo today that the day 
before yesterday, security authorities asked al-Mahdi about the 
party's activities at home and abroad, his 'Id al-Fitr sermon, 
and his continuing refusal to reconcile with the ruling regime. 
  The statement said: "The arrest reaffirms the confusion and 
tension experienced by the regime after losing every 
justification for survival." 
  The statement appealed to the world community, human rights 
organizations, and Arab and non-Arab media to pressure the 
Sudanese regime to release al-Mahdi and all Sudanese prisoners 
immediately. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

