<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemeni Foreign Minister Arrives in Tehran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemeni Foreign Minister Arrives in Tehran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704192894 Tehran IRNA in English 1637 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 7, IRNA -- Foreign Minister of Yemen 
Muhammad Salim Basindwah arrived here Thursday with a message 
from Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih for President Akbar 
Hashemi- Rafsanjani. He was welcomed by his Iranian counterpart 
'Ali Akbar Velayati. 
  Upon arrival at the airport Basindwah called for the 
strengthening of Tehran-Sanaa relations which he said date back 
to pre-Islamic era. He [word indistinct] confident that the two 
countries will enter into a new era of cooperation through 
further expansion of their brotherly ties. 
  As for the differences between Yemeni president and the 
vice-president, Salih said the situation in Yemen was not so bad 
as reflected by foreign mass media outside that country. 
Commenting on the likelihood of Iran's mediation efforts, he 
said that Yemen welcomed all mediation efforts. However, he 
said, the issue of Yemen could be solved solely by Yemenis 
themselves. 

</TEXT>

