Persian 1530 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a speedy reaction, the UN secretary general and 
the Security Council have condemned the martyrdom-seeking action 
of a revolutionary Muslim Palestinian at 'Afula. 
  The representative of Hamas, the Islamic Resistance 
Movement, 
in Tehran described the stance of the UN Security Council as 
spiteful. He said: This proves that the Palestinian nation 
should not expect sympathy from the United Nations or the 
Security Council, because they have always remained silent in 
the face of the daily murder of Palestinian women and children 
by the Zionists. 

</TEXT>

