<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jannati Leads Friday Prayers; Criticizes U.S. `Pressures' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jannati Leads Friday Prayers; Criticizes U.S. `Pressures' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804101994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In his Friday prayer sermons, Ayatollah Ahmad 
Jannati, the acting Friday imam of Tehran, said that the 
martyrdom-seeking attack by a Palestinian youth was a clear 
example of the uprising of Muslims against the arrogance's 
injustice and oppression. 
  He referred to the compromise plans in connection with the 
Palestinian issue and said: Compromise by claimants to 
leadership of Palestine does not solve any of the Zionist 
regime's problems. 
  In his second sermon, Ayatollah Jannati referred to the 
emphasis by the eminent leader [Khamene'i] on the importance of 
work ethics, the social order, and a serious attitude towards 
work. He said that the lack of such an attitude constituted one 
of the shortcomings of the society, and called for greater 
efforts in this area. 
  He then alluded to the grave responsibilities of the Voice 
and Vision of the Islamic Republic of Iran as a medium for 
communications. He stressed the need for greater efforts, as 
well as more help for that organization, so as to enable it to 
provide a more valuable service. 
  The acting Friday imam of Tehran then set out to describe 
all 
the pressures exerted by America with the aim of forcing the 
Islamic Republic of Iran to surrender. He stressed once again 
that the Iranian nation would never surrender to tyranny and 
oppression. 

</TEXT>

