<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijani Foreign Minister Gasanov Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azerbaijani Foreign Minister Gasanov Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Mubarak </H4>

<F P=102> NC0804191394 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0804191394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Azerbaijani Foreign Minister Gasan Gasanov, who is 
on an official visit to Egypt, was received yesterday by 
Egyptian President Husni Mubarak. The minister presented the 
Azerbaijani president's letter to Husni Mubarak. The question 
of expanding bilateral ties were discussed at the meeting. 
Gasan Gasanov briefed Husni Mubarak in detail on the Armenian 
aggression. Husni Mubarak stated that Egypt resolutely condemns 
this aggression and wants the ouster of the occupationist forces 
from the Azerbaijani lands as soon as possible and the peaceful 
settlement of the conflict. He noted that Egypt, and he 
personally, opposes the forcible change of borders. President 
Husni Mubarak said that the Egyptian people regard the 
Azerbaijani people as friendly and fraternal. He hoped that 
Azerbaijan President Geydar Aliyev's official visit to Egypt 
will help further improve relations between our countries. 
  Gasan Gasanov also visited the Arab League, met Secretary 
General 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid, and provided detailed information 
to him on the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict and gave him an 
information package to be sent to the members of the Arab 
League. Gasan Gasanov addressed the Arab League's extraordinary 
session on 7 April. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

