<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Information Minister, UAE Minister Leave for Sanaa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Information Minister, UAE Minister Leave for Sanaa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0904121294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1140 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0904121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 9 Apr (MENA)--Information Minister Safwat 
al-Sharif and Rashid Bin-'Abdallah al-Na'imi, United Arab 
Emirates [UAE] foreign minister, left Cairo for Sanaa today as 
envoys of President Husni Mubarak and UAE President Shaykh Zayid 
Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan. They are scheduled to meet with Yemeni 
President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih this evening and Vice President 
'Ali Salim al-Bid tomorrow morning. 
  The visit is part of the efforts made by President Mubarak 
and Shaykh Zayid to contain the Yemeni crisis. Assistant 
Foreign Minister Badr Hammam is accompanying al-Sharif and 
al-Na'imi on their visit. 
  Earlier today, President Mubarak received a message from 
Shaykh Zayid during his meeting with UAE Foreign Minister 
al-Na'imi. 
  Al-Sharif stated that the message deals with the joint 
efforts by President Mubarak and Shaykh Zayid to find a solution 
for the Yemeni crisis by bringing the views of the Yemeni 
political leaders closer together. 

</TEXT>

