<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Musa, PRC Ambassador Discuss Mideast, Korea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa, PRC Ambassador Discuss Mideast, Korea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0904143294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1320 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0904143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 9 Apr (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
received Chinese Ambassador to Cairo Yang Fuchang today. 
  The Chinese ambassador said after the meeting that his 
country welcomes President Husni Mubarak's visit to China. He 
added that Mubarak's visit to his country comes when strong 
relations link the two countries and hoped that the visit will 
promote and develop the ties between the two friendly countries. 
  He emphasized that the two countries' views on various world 
issues are identical and stressed China's support for the Middle 
East peace process. He expressed his hope that a comprehensive 
and just peace will be achieved in the region and said his 
country is trying to advance the peace process. 
  The ambassador said China supports the need for the Korean 
Peninsula to be free of all nuclear weapons and for the problem 
between the two Koreas to be resolved through negotiations. 

</TEXT>

