<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lebanese Forces Implicated in Plot To Kill President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lebanese Forces Implicated in Plot To Kill President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1004062294 London MBC Television in Arabic 2320 GMT 9 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1004062294 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Military Court investigators in Lebanon have 
interrogated Lebanese Army Sergeant Sharfan Bulus and two former 
members of the disbanded Lebanese Forces accused of plotting to 
kill President Ilyas al-Hirawi. 
  Lebanese judiciary sources say that the Military Court will 
try Ghassan Tuma, head of the Lebanese Forces' security 
apparatus, in absentia. Tuma asked Sergeant Bulus, a bomb 
expert working at the Presidential Palace, about the possibility 
of planting a bomb, the target of which would be the president, 
in a flower vase, a car, or a telephone set, according to the 
same sources. 

</TEXT>

