<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Security Activities, Conflicts in South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Security Activities, Conflicts in South </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kafra, Yatar Shelled; Lahd Unit Ambushed </H4>

<F P=102> NC0604170694 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The outskirts of the towns of Kafra and Yatar have 
been coming under shelling since 1530 today from the occupation 
center in Jabal Humayyid. A center belonging to the Nepalese 
contingent in Yatar was hit by machine-gun fire coming from the 
Lahd agents' post in the occupied strip opposite the town. The 
Martyr Husayn Nasir Mahdi group of the Islamic Resistance laid 
an ambush for a Lahdist security convoy on the Bayt Lif road. 
The strugglers showered the convoy's cars with a hail of fire 
from machine guns and artillery. Several artillery shells hit 
the car transporting the security officials. It was burnt out 
immediately and its occupants were either killed or injured. 

</TEXT>

