<H4>    Israeli Shelling, Overflights, Gunboats </H4>

<F P=102> NC0804094894 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0900 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0804094894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Lebanese Army's deserted barracks in 
al-Nabatiyah came under an artillery barrage from Israeli 
positions in Tallat 'Ali al-Tahir at 0945 today. The barrage 
was accompanied by bursts of heavy machine-gun fire from 
adjacent hills and valleys. Rounds landed in the vicinity of 
al-Mansuri from Israeli positions in al- Bayyadah. 
  Israeli helicopters flew over the area at midnight last 
night, illuminating the area from al-Mansuri, Majdal Zun, 
Zibqin, and Kafra, up to Yatar. 
  An Israeli gunboat cruised the coast of Tyre. Head of the 
fishermen syndicate in Tyre said that the fishermen are 
encountering difficulties fishing because Israeli gunboats 
intercept their fishing boats. 

</TEXT>

