<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Security Activities, Conflicts in South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Security Activities, Conflicts in South </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Palestinians Attack SLA </H4>

<F P=102> NC0804202194 Paris AFP in English 1914 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0804202194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sidon, Lebanon, April 8 (AFP)--Two radical 
Palestinian factions said they attacked a militia patrol in 
south Lebanon Friday. 
  The Popular and Democratic Fronts for the Liberation of 
Palestine said in a joint statement that they fired on a patrol 
of Israel's proxy South Lebanon Army (SLA) in the west of 
Israel's self-declared security zone. 
  The statement said the factions blew up an armored vehicle, 
killing or wounding its crew. 
  Voice of the South radio said a civilian vehicle had been 
attacked close to Shqif al-Naml without causing any victims. 
  Security services confirmed an SLA patrol had come under 
fire 
but could not give details of any casualties. 
  The two factions are opposed to the Middle East peace 
process 
and the Israel-Palestine Liberation Organisation autonomy accord 
signed in Washington in September. 

</TEXT>

