<H3> <TI>   Shells Kill 3 `Resistance Fighters' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shells Kill 3 `Resistance Fighters' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0904170394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1542 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0904170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Just in from the editor's desk: According to a 
REUTER report a short while ago, three resistance fighters were 
killed and three others were injured when Israeli forces this 
afternoon bombarded the vicinity of Tallat 'Ali al-Tahir, which 
is occupied by Israeli forces. REUTER also reported that 
Israeli helicopters flew several sorties over Kafr Tibnit and 
released dozens of thermal balloons. 
  The Israeli forces heated up the security situation in the 
south this afternoon. At 1550, Israeli forces began bombarding 
al-Nabatiyah al-Fawqa, the outskirts of the Lebanese army's 
deserted barracks in al-Nabatiyah, the outskirts of Kafr Tibnit, 
Arnun, the 'Ali al-Tahir wood, and al-Dabshah. The shelling was 
followed by intensive machine-gun fire from Israeli positions. 
Hostile tank movement was spotted in al-Dabshah. After 1630, 
the shelling reached the outskirts of the Ghandur Palace and 
Tallat al-Mazra'ah in the al-Nabatiyah al-Fawqa area. The 
shelling was accompanied by 12.7-mm machine-gun fire from the 
Israeli positions in the 'Ali al- Tahir hills and al-Dabshah. 

</TEXT>

