  [Text] Our military correspondent reports that a 
terrorist cell opened fire on an Israeli army post in 'Ali 
al-Tahir area yesterday afternoon. Immediately afterward, the 
Israeli army carried out a wide-scale combing operation in which 
helicopters and tanks took part. 
  Meanwhile, South Lebanese Army personnel [SLA] manning a 
tank 
positioned in Kafr Rumman discovered the cell as it was entering 
a red stone villa in the town. The SLA soldiers shelled the 
cell, killing three elements from the Popular Front for the 
Liberation of Palestine [PFLP] and wounding three others. 

