<H3> <TI>   Members to Joint Committees With PLO Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Members to Joint Committees With PLO Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1104095294 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 11 Apr 94 pp 1, 27 </F>
<F P=103> JN1104095294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman -- AL-DUSTUR has learned that from the premise 
of its belief in action and the formation of joint committees 
between it and the fraternal Arab countries, Jordan has 
completed for its part the formation of the joint coordination 
committees between it and the PLO. The following are the names 
of the members of these committees: 
  1. The Jordanian-PLO higher ministerial coordination 
committee under Sa'id al-Tall, deputy prime minister and 
minister of Higher Education, and the following as members: 
Jawad al-'Anani, minister of state for Cabinet Affairs and 
information minister; Dr. Ziyad Fariz, minister of planning; 
Mahdi al-Farhan, minister of Agriculture; Salamah Hammad, 
Interior Minister; and Talal Sat'an al-Hasan, minister of state 
for foreign affairs. 
  2. The Jerusalem Committee is made up of the following: 'Izz 
al- Din al-Khatib al-Tamimi, his majesty's adviser and Chief 
Justice; Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-'Abbadi, minister of Awqaf and 
Islamic Affairs; and ambassador 'Awn al-Khasawinah, adviser to 
the crown prince. 
  3. The economic committee comprises the following: Dr. 
Safwan Tuqan, secretary general of the Planning Ministry; Dr. 
Michel Martu, Jordanian Central Bank deputy governor; Musa 
al-Jaghbir, Customs Department assistant director general, and 
Safwan al-Batayinah, director of the prime ministry's economic 
department. 
  The committee on refugees and the displaced is made up of: 
Marwan Dudin; Khalil Khuraysat, Interior Ministry secretary 
general; Ambassador Nayif al-Hadid, Foreign Ministry secretary 
general; and Muhammad Shahinkari, from the Foreign Ministry. 
  The committee on security and borders comprises Dr. 
'Abdallah 
Tuqan, his majesty's adviser on scientific affairs; Major 
General Tahsin Shurdum, deputy chief of staff; and Major General 
Muhammad al-Bassul, Public Security Department assistant 
director. 
  AL-DUSTUR has also learned that that the Palestinian side, 
as 
yet, has not communicated to Jordan the names of the Palestinian 
members on these committees. 

</TEXT>

