<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Saudi Arabia </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Source' Denies Troops Enter Yemeni Territory </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Source' Denies Troops Enter Yemeni Territory </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0904121594 Riyadh SPA in Arabic 0015 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0904121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, 7 Apr -- In response to claims by the Yemeni 
paper AL-HIWAR, which stated that Saudi forces had penetrated 
five kilometers inside Yemeni territory, an official source at 
the Ministry of Defense, Aviation and the Inspectorate General 
said: The entire report of this paper is fabricated and has no 
foundation of truth. Yemeni officials themselves are aware of 
the extent of the falsity of the content of the newspaper's 
report. 
  The source added: As regard the other topics created by the 
said paper, they are, in our view, unworthy of any mention or 
consideration. 
  At the end of the statement the source said: While we are 
clarifying the truth to refute these claims, we underline the 
strength of the relations that link the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia 
and the Yemeni Republic. 

</TEXT>

