<H3> <TI>   Egyptian, UAE Ministers Arrive With Message </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Egyptian, UAE Ministers Arrive With Message </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0904174494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0904174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Rashid Bin-'Abdallah, foreign minister of 
the United Arab Emirates [UAE], and Safwat al-Sharif, Egyptian 
information minister, arrived in Sanaa today on a visit to our 
country. They will meet with brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council. 
  In a statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', Egyptian 
Information Minister Safwat al-Sharif said he and his brother, 
Rashid Bin-'Abdallah, are carrying a joint message from 
President Mubarak and Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan to 
bring Yemeni views closer so Yemen will remain within the Arab 
fold. The letter also represents joint Arab efforts. 
  The joint delegation was received by brother Dr. 
'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, minister of planning and development; 
Hasan al-Lawzi, minister of information; and the Egyptian and 
UAE ambassador in Sanaa. 

</TEXT>

