  [Text] President Hashemi-Rafsanjani today received Yemeni 
Foreign Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah. The president 
described the strengthening of cooperation between Iran and 
Yemen as being important in helping to safeguard the security 
and stability of the region. Stressing the need for 
strengthening the unity of the two Yemens, the president 
announced the Islamic Republic of Iran's readiness to help in 
this matter. 
  At the start of the meeting, the Yemeni foreign minister 
offered the warmest greetings from the president, government, 
and people of his country to the government and people of Iran. 
He described relations between the two countries as deep-rooted 
and historic. He expressed the interest of the government and 
people of Yemen in strengthening these relations. After 
reporting on the latest developments in Yemen, on behalf of the 
Yemeni president, he invited Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani to visit 
Yemen. 

