<H4>    Meets With Other Officials </H4>

<F P=102> JN1004074494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1004074494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A round of Yemeni-Iranian talks was held in Tehran 
this evening. The talks were headed on the Yemeni side by 
Foreign Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah and on the Irani side 
by Iranian Foreign Minister Dr. 'Ali Akbar Velayati. Delegation 
members of both sides attended. 
  During the meeting, issues of common interest were reviewed. 
The two sides also discussed bilateral ties and the means of 
promoting them. 
  In a related development, the foreign minister and his 
delegation met with Iranian Commerce Minister Yahya ol-Eshaq at 
the Ministry of Commerce in Tehran at noon today. The talks 
addressed the fraternal bilateral ties, and the means of 
promoting them. 
  Afterward, the foreign minister met with Iranian Culture and 
Higher Education Minister Mohammad Reza Hashemi-Golpayegani. 
The talks addressed the prospects for promoting bilateral 
cooperation. 
  The two meetings were attended by the Yemeni ambassador in 
Tehran and the Iranian ambassador in Sanaa. 
  Foreign Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah also met with 
Construction Jihad Minister Gholam Reza Foruzesh in Tehran this 
evening. They discussed bilateral ties as well as issues of 
common interest to the two fraternal states. 
  The meeting was attended by the delegation accompanying the 
foreign minister, several officials of the Ministry of 
Construction Jihad, our ambassador in Tehran, and the Iranian 
ambassador to our country. 

</TEXT>

