<H3> <TI>   Paris Embassy Denies Arms Supplied to Algeria's FIS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paris Embassy Denies Arms Supplied to Algeria's FIS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0904131194 Tehran IRNA in English 1222 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0904131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, 9 April, IRNA -- The Iranian Embassy in 
Paris has denied allegations that Iran ever provided any arms to 
the Islamic Salvation Front (FIS) of Algeria. 
  In a statement issued on Friday, the Iranian embassy denied 
claims raised by the French daily `LE FIGARO' on Iran's possible 
involvement in arms supply to FIS. 
  According to official reports released here an Israeli-made 
assault rifle has been found in the house of an Algerian 
national in Paris which was searched by the French police. 
  In the past, certain segments of western mass media have 
tried to justify the West's support for the military-installed 
government in Algeria by accusing foreign countries of 
involvement in the Islamic movement of the Algerian people. 

</TEXT>

