<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Meets Palestinian Police Coordinator </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Meets Palestinian Police Coordinator </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804182194 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 8 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother President Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] 
received yesterday evening Mr. (Larsen), general coordinator of 
the Special Committee for Palestinian police who was accompanied 
by officials in charge of the international presence in Hebron 
from Norway, Denmark, and Italy. 
  The meetings was also attended by brothers Abu-Mazin [Mahmud 
'Abbas], Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, Dr. Nabil Sha'th, and Hebron Mayor 
Mustafa al- Natshah and the members of its Municipal Council. 
  The practical steps and the mechanisms of the deployment of 
this international presence in Hebron, in implementation of UN 
Security Council's Resolution 904, were discussed during the 
meeting. 
  Brother President Abu-'Ammar stressed the importance of the 
international role in providing protection to our people and 
ending the siege and the curfew that has been imposed on the 
city by the Israeli Army for more than 40 days. He also 
emphasized the importance of the city's return to normal life. 
  The brother president expressed the PLO's eagerness to 
cooperate and coordinate with these forces, particularly as the 
brother mayor is the representative of brother President 
Abu-'Ammar to the joint committee in Hebron in charge of 
cooperation with the international presence. 

</TEXT>

