Daily Report 
<DATE1>  10 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Cited on Economic Situation, Workers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Cited on Economic Situation, Workers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1004124694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1203 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1004124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 10 Apr (MENA)--Palestinian information 
sources have stated that President Yasir 'Arafat chaired a 
meeting of the Palestinian leadership yesterday and the day 
before yesterday to discuss the deteriorating economic situation 
of the Palestinians due to the Israeli blockade that has been 
imposed on the occupied territories for 45 days. This blockade, 
the sources added, was causing poverty and hunger in the 
territories. 
  The sources said that 'Arafat briefed the participants on 
the 
reports that he had received from Palestinian officials in Gaza 
and Hebron. The reports indicated that poverty and hunger have 
spread due to the Israeli military blockade and the ban on 
130,000 Palestinian workers from reporting to their work inside 
Israel. 
  According to the sources, 'Arafat had taken a number of 
urgent measures to avert further exacerbation of the crisis and 
to foil the Israeli attempt to import workers from abroad to 
replace the Palestinian workers, who are prevented from going to 
their work in Israel. 
  The sources said that, during his meeting with the 
ambassadors of the UN Security Council permanent member states 
in Cairo last week, 'Arafat briefed them on the tragic condition 
of well over two million Palestinians. 'Arafat told the envoys 
that this condition has been caused by Israel's disregard of its 
international commitments and its evasion of implementing the 
articles of the Palestinian-Israeli Declaration of Principles. 
'Arafat voiced his stern rejection of Israel's extortionist 
policy, according to the sources. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

