BFN 

  [Text] Brother Marwan Kanafani, adviser to brother 
Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], president of the state of Palestine 
and chairman of the PLO Executive Committee, made the following 
statement: 
  It is very strange to hear this kind of logic from Shimon 
Peres, Israeli foreign affairs minister, especially because 
neither he nor Prime Minister Rabin have expressed any kind of 
regret and condemnation when the Israeli army and intelligence 
deliberately assassinated six young leaders from the Fatah 
Movement in Gaza recently. On the contrary, the Israeli housing 
minister expressed his appreciation and that of the government 
and the Israeli army for this kind of terrorist act immediately 
after the weekly meeting of the Israeli cabinet. 

