<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   DFLP, PFLP Leadership Demands 'Arafat Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DFLP, PFLP Leadership Demands 'Arafat Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0904124894 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1200 GMT 9 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0904124894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nayif Hawatimah, secretary general of the Democratic 
Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP], has said that the 
growing popular Palestinian resistance will wreck the Oslo and 
Cairo agreements. He stressed that it is impossible to coexist 
with the settlements and that there is no alternative to the 
removal of the occupation. Nayif Hawatimah renewed his 
criticism of the Palestinian leadership, which, he said, has 
ceded all the Palestinian people's demands after the Hebron 
massacre. 
  Meanwhile, the unified central leadership of the Popular 
Front for the Liberation of Palestine [PFLP] and the DFLP 
demanded PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat and his team resign. It 
condemned the occupation authorities' decision to close the 
occupied Palestinian territories, deeming it a collective 
detention of the Palestinian people. 

</TEXT>

