<H3> <TI>   Palestinian-Israeli Talks Resume in Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian-Israeli Talks Resume in Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sha'th: Negotiations `Positive' </H4>

<F P=102> NC1104060094 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0500 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1104060094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Palestinian-Israeli negotiations on the 
implementation of the self-rule agreement will resume in Cairo 
this morning, just days before the date set for the Israeli 
withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho on 13 April. The two sides 
held talks all day yesterday, with chief Palestinian negotiator 
Nabil Sha'th describing the negotiations as positive. But 
Sha'th declined to give any details of progress in the talks. 

</TEXT>

