<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Sends `Urgent' Message to UK, France </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Sends `Urgent' Message to UK, France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804174294 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 8 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The brother president Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] 
received his excellency the British ambassador in Cairo 
yesterday evening. He gave him an important and urgent verbal 
message for the British Government related to the impasse 
reached by the negotiations with regard to implementing the 
agreement on the declaration of principles because of the 
obstacles placed by Israel in the way of implementing the 
agreement, which threatens the peace process. 
  The brother president also sent an important and urgent 
message to President Mitterrand and the French Government, 
related to the impasse reached by the negotiations with regard 
to the implementation of the agreement on the declaration of 
principles because of the obstacles placed by the Israeli 
Government in the way of implementing the agreement within the 
fixed deadlines. 

</TEXT>

