<H3> <TI>   Qaddumi Noncommittal on Chances for Talks' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qaddumi Noncommittal on Chances for Talks' </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Success 

<F P=102>   JN0804122594 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 7 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0804122594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Faruq Qaddumi, head of the PLO's Political 
Department, has said that he explored with top officials in 
Hanoi prospects for Vietnam helping in the effort to 
rehabilitate the Palestinian economy and infrastructure, which 
has been destroyed by the Israelis. Qaddumi was speaking at a 
news conference shortly before departing Ho Chi Minh City 
airport at the conclusion of a three-day visit yesterday. 
Qaddumi reached agreements with top Vietnamese officials about 
economic cooperation. Vietnam, he added, can help in the area 
of technical expertise and personnel training. 
  Asked to evaluate the chances of the ongoing talks between 
Palestinians and Israelis in Cairo, brother Qaddumi said he was 
neither optimistic nor pessimistic. Calling the talks tough, he 
said the Israelis are delaying [words indistinct] withdrawal 
from the occupied Palestinian territories. 

</TEXT>

