<DATE1>  11 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy to U.S.: Pakistan `Continues To Interfere' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoy to U.S.: Pakistan `Continues To Interfere' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1104041694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1104041694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] India's ambassador to the United States, Mr. 
Siddhartha Shankar Ray, says that Pakistan continues to 
interfere in the internal affairs of India. He said he has 
collected evidence of this during his two-day visit to Jammu and 
Kashmir. Mr. Ray was talking to newspersons in New Delhi. He 
said the evidence collected relates to the foreign mercenaries 
in Kashmir, foreign arms and ammunition seized, and the location 
of camps where the Pakistan authorities have been training 
terrorists. The ambassador said approximately 44,000 Hindus, 
Sikh, and Muslim families have fled the valley because of the 
militant activities. 
  Mr. Ray said the delivery of more F-16 aircraft to Islamabad 
by Washington will not reduce tension in South Asia nor will it 
promote any dialogue between India and Pakistan. He warned the 
United States that if it does not desist from this course, the 
arms race in the subcontinent will be fueled. 

</TEXT>

