<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   D'Souza Reinstalled as Chief Minister of Goa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    D'Souza Reinstalled as Chief Minister of Goa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0904074994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0904074994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Wilfred D'Souza has been reinstalled as the 
chief minister of Goa. He was administered the oath of office 
and secrecy by the governor, Mr. B. Rachaiah, in Panaji this 
evening. Five other ministers also took office. They are: Mr. 
Vasu Paik Gaonkar, Mr. Suresh Parulekar, Mr. Ashok Naik 
Salgaonkar, Dr. (Karno Pigado), and Mr. Vinay Kumar Usgaonkar. 
  Talking to newspersons after the swearing-in ceremony, the 
chief minister said he will act according to the wishes of the 
party high command on the induction of five dissident ministers 
who resigned last week. 

</TEXT>

