<H3> <TI>   INSAT 2-C To Use KU Band To Receive Signals From Satellites </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    INSAT 2-C To Use KU Band To Receive Signals From Satellites </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1104091694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0435 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1104091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Indian National Satellite -- INSAT 2-C will be 
launched during the middle of next year. The annual report of 
the Department of Space says that the INSAT 2-C and INSAT 2-D 
will be much different from the earlier INSAT series. The INSAT 
2-C will use for the first time KU band which will help in 
receiving signals from satellites through small dish antenna. 

</TEXT>

