  [Excerpts] [Announcer] Mr. [Ahmad] Nateq-Nuri, speaker of 
the Islamic Consultative Majles, arrived in Islamabad today at 
the head of a senior political and economic delegation following 
an invitation from his Pakistani counterpart. Our colleague 
reports from Pakistan: 
  [Unidentified correspondent] [passage omitted] On the aims 
of 
his visit, Mr. Nateq-Nuri said: 
  [Begin Nateq-Nuri recording] We are going to discuss 
economic 
issues during this visit. Therefore, the esteemed petroleum 
minister [Gholam Reza Aqazadeh-Kho'i] and the honorable roads 
