<H3> <TI>   Addresses National Assembly </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Addresses National Assembly </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104095794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the second day of his visit to Pakistan, Mr. 
Nateq-Nuri, speaker of the Islamic Consultative Majles, today 
addressed the Pakistani National Assembly on the issues facing 
the Islamic world. He described the all-encompassing cultural 
and propaganda onslaught of the West against Islam and the 
West's double standards toward the world of Islam as a warning, 
indicative of the policy of confronting and attacking Islam. He 
stressed: In today's world, the message of Islamic countries is 
that they should defend the revivalist movement of Islam and 
never bow to the pressures and political and nonpolitical 
propaganda of the world of blasphemy. 
  Mr. Nateq-Nuri also announced the Islamic Republic of Iran's 
support for any proposal that encompasses the rights of the 
Kashmiri people. 

</TEXT>

