<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Austrian President Klestil, Delegation Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Austrian President Klestil, Delegation Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Economic Talks Held </H4>

<F P=102> JN1004170294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1004170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A meeting between a Syrian economic delegation led 
by Dr. 'Abd-al-Rahim Subay'i, [minister of state for planning 
affairs], and an Austrian economic delegation led by Dr. (Erich 
Betman), assistant minister for economic affairs at the Ministry 
of Public Economy and Transport, was held at the State Planning 
Commission this morning. 
  Talks focused on ways to promote and enhance bilateral 
economic, trade, and technical relations by benefiting from the 
large available capabilities. The two sides stressed the 
importance of establishing joint firms in fields of common 
interest, as well as benefiting from Austrian experience by 
training Syrian cadres and promoting bilateral trade exchanges. 
  The meeting was attended by representatives from the 
concerned ministries, establishments, and chambers of commerce, 
as well as Syrian and Austrian businessmen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

