<H3> <TI>   Bombs Reportedly Explode Near 2 Ministries in Baghdad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bombs Reportedly Explode Near 2 Ministries in Baghdad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0804123894 Paris AFP in English 1049 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0804123894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman, 8 April (AFP)--Bombs exploded 15 minutes 
apart near Iraqi ministries in Baghdad on Wednesday, an Iraqi 
group said here Friday without reporting casualties. 
  "An explosive device was placed at al-Nidal Street about 100 
meters (300 feet) from the Industry Ministry and another was 
placed near the agriculture and Irrigation Ministry," the Iraqi 
National Congress said in a statement. 
  "The two explosions caused panic among security services and 
coincided with the anniversary of the foundation of the ruling 
(Ba'th) party," said the statement dated from Sulaymaniyah and 
Kurdish-controlled norther Iraq. 
  It said the first occurred at 5:30 a.m. (0130 GMT) and the 
second at 5:45 a.m. (0145 GMT). 

</TEXT>

