in Arabic 1430 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0904191594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a report from inside Iraq, our sources say that a 
group of the Islamic resistance threw three hand grenades at the 
al-Nasiriyah governor's headquarters during his meeting with 
security and intelligence officials. The sources say the 
resulting explosion inflicted material damage on the building, 
wounded a number of its guards, and prompted the governor and 
the regime's henchmen to hide in an underground shelter. 
  In another development, the resistance dealt a destructive 
blow to the district officer's headquarters in al-Nasiriyah on 
the evening of 18 March. Various types of light and medium 
weapons and mortars were used. Our sources confirm that eight 
regime elements were killed and others wounded. Heavy damage 
was inflicted on the building, which the regime uses as a center 
for its mercenaries and criminals who monitor the citizens' 
movements and arrest them. 

</TEXT>

