<H3> <TI>   Ranking Military Officer Defects to U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ranking Military Officer Defects to U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1004102094 Kuwait AL-RA'Y AL-'AMM in Arabic 2 Apr 94 pp 1, 
19 </F>

<F P=103> JN1004102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait AL-RA'Y AL-'AMM </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] AL-RA'Y AL-'AMM has learned from exclusive sources 
that a ranking Iraqi officer who was very close to Saddam Husayn 
has defected to the United States through Turkey after doubts 
were cast on his role in the attempt to topple the regime that 
was discovered two months ago, following which a number of 
ranking military commanders were executed. 
  These sources said the officer had played a central role in 
preparing for the invasion of Kuwait, and was directly 
responsible for all cash payments and gifts that were given to 
top officials and a large number of journalists in some Arab 
countries in order to extend material and moral support for the 
Iraqi adventure against Kuwait. 
  AL-RA'Y AL-'AMM also learned that the Iraqi officer will 
hold a news conference soon to reveal in figures and names the 
huge sums of money the Iraqi regime had given to some political 
and military officials and journalists shortly before the 
treacherous invasion. 

</TEXT>

