<H3> <TI>   Baghdad Protests Saudi, Kuwaiti Bases for Allied Aircraft </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baghdad Protests Saudi, Kuwaiti Bases for Allied Aircraft </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0404114994 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1130 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0404114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iraq has informed the Arab League that the Saudi and 
Kuwaiti rulers continue to grant facilities to the U.S., 
British, and French aircraft for violating Iraqi airspace and 
threatening Iraq's security, sovereignty, and national unity. 
  In a letter he addressed to the Arab League secretary 
general 
yesterday, Iraq's Arab League permanent representative said that 
these aircraft continued to violate Iraqi airspace 25-30 April 
from their bases in Saudi Arabia and Kuwait, and carried out 233 
hostile air sorties. 
  A list appended to the letter explains these violations in 
detail. 

</TEXT>

