<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mosul Reported `Tense'; Opposition To Meet 16 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mosul Reported `Tense'; Opposition To Meet 16 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704173394 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0704173394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An Iraqi opposition source in Damascus has stated 
that the Iraqi regime forces have tightened the cordon they 
imposed on Mosul in anticipation of civil disobedience by the 
city's inhabitants. 
  Bayan Jabir, the Supreme Assembly of the Islamic Revolution 
in Iraq's representative in Damascus, said the situation in the 
city is very tense. He added that the executive committee of 
the Unified Iraqi National Congress will meet in Salah-al-Din in 
Iraqi Kurdistan on 16 April to discuss the deteriorating 
situation in Iraq in light of these developments. 

</TEXT>

