<F P=102>   JN0804090494 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0720 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0804090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Baghdad, 8 Apr (INA) -- 'Abd-al-Ghani 
'Abd-al-Ghafur, member of the Iraq Command of the Arab Socialist 
Ba'th Party, has returned to Baghdad after a visit of several 
days to Moscow, where he held talks with Russian Government 
officials and party leaders. 
  In an arrival statement to the Iraqi News Agency, 
'Abd-al-Ghafur said Russian party chiefs are impressed by the 
pace of Iraq's renewal, led by President Saddam Husayn, who has 
turned into a symbol of the fight against imperialist hegemony. 
  'Abd-al-Ghafur said he hoped that when the UN Security 
Council next reviews Iraq's compliance with Paragraph 22 of 
Resolution 687 calling for lifting the sanctions, Russia will 
adopt an even more postitive attitude. Iraq, he noted, had 
fulfilled the obligations stipulated by the council resolutions, 
unfair as they are. 
  Russian Government officials and party leaders emphasized 
that retention of the sanctions hurts not only the Iraqi people 
but Russia as well. They reiterated Russia's willingness to 
maintain excellent relations with Iraq, 'Abd-al-Ghafur added. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

