<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Defers Decision on Duration of Closure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Defers Decision on Duration of Closure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1004113994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 10 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1004113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The cabinet is getting ready for a prolonged 
closure of the territories. Our political correspondent Shlomo 
Raz reports that the cabinet today decided to keep the closure 
in effect until after Independence Day and to discuss its 
duration and magnitude in its meeting next week. 
  The cabinet also consented to import 18,000 foreign workers: 
15,000 in construction and 3,000 in agriculture. They will 
begin working within three to five weeks and will be issued 
six-month work permits. It was also decided to subsidize the 
employment of 4,000 foreign workers in agriculture, including 
2,000 who are already working in this sector. 
  The cabinet decided to set up a team to examine the plan to 
employ high school students and soldiers in agriculture until 
the foreign workers arrive. The prime minister said in the 
meeting that we should rid ourselves of our dependence on 
laborers from the territories, a dependence which forces us to 
decisions which endanger the security of the citizens. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

