<F P=102>   TA0904143194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 9 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0904143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] PLO official Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh has called for 
immediate negotiations on the permanent status of the 
territories instead of continuing the talks on Palestinian 
autonomy in the Gaza Strip and Jericho. 
  In an interview with correspondents in Tunis, 'Abd-Rabbuh 
said that the agreement between the PLO and Israel was dying and 
the diplomatic process was reaching a dead end. 
  In reaction, political sources in Jerusalem said that it was 
the Israeli Government's policy to honor agreements. Therefore, 
there was no point in discussing the next stage of the 
negotiations between the PLO and Israel before the talks on 
Gaza-Jericho First were completed. 

