<H3> <TI>   Observers' Advance Team Meets With Hebron Mayor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Observers' Advance Team Meets With Hebron Mayor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1104070294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0600 GMT 11 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1104070294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning, 10 representatives of the Danish, 
Norwegian, and Italian observers met with Hebron Mayor Mustafa 
al- Natshah in the city. At the end of the meeting, the mayor 
said he hopes the observers will be able to separate the Arab 
residents of Hebron and the settlers. 
  Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that Khalid 'Amayirah, 
the chief Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] spokesman, 
attacked the presence of the observers in the city and said this 
is merely a public relations stunt. He warned that if the 
residents of Hebron do not feel a change in their security, the 
force might be in danger. 
  The head of the Norwegian delegation said that his men were 
received warmly in Hebron and that the mayor briefed him on the 
city's problems. He expressed the hope that the observers force 
will be able to start working soon. 

