<F P=103> TA1004051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A senior military source is quoted by the ITIM news 
agency as confirming that the Israeli Army is preparing for the 
possibility that the Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] 
organization will follow through on its threat to launch missile 
attacks against Israeli targets. Hamas has threatened that 
among the attacks it intends to carry out in advance of 
Independence Day will be missile launchings against targets that 
include Israeli settlements in the territories. The military 
source told ITIM that there is little doubt that Hamas has the 
ability to use missiles, primarily LAW antitank missiles that 
are easy to carry and that are widely used by the Israeli Army. 

