<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Renews Threat To Kill Jewish Settlers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Renews Threat To Kill Jewish Settlers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1104140194 Paris AFP in English 1230 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1104140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gaza City, Occupied Gaza Strip, April 11 (AFP)--The 
Islamic Resistance Movement [Hamas] Monday [11 April] renewed a 
threat to murder Jewish settlers and said a suicide attack that 
left seven Israelis dead and 45 wounded was only a beginning. 
  A leaflet distributed in Gaza warned that the group's 
military wing, 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam, has "decided to hit at 
settlers so they can get a taste of death and leave our land." 
  "The 'Afula operation is only a beginning," it said. 
  A Hamas suicide bomber last Wednesday blew up a bus in 
'Afula. 
  A day after the bombing, Hamas threatened to fire rockets at 
Israeli homes and said the attack was the first of five to come 
on Israeli targets. 
  Meanwhile, the body of a Palestinian man with a bullet hole 
in his head was dumped in the street in Gaza City. Palestinian 
sources said he had been executed by Hamas for collaborating 
with Israeli authorities. 

</TEXT>

