<H3> <TI>   IDF Officers Train for Patrols With Palestinians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Officers Train for Patrols With Palestinians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1104054294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 11 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1104054294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Thirty IDF [Israel Defense Forces] infantry and 
tank officers have begun a course preparing them for joint 
patrols with the Palestinian police in the Gaza Strip. 
According to Qol Yisra'el's military correspondent, the course 
centers on the jeep patrols which will take place: one vehicle 
with IDF soldiers, the other with Palestinian police. 
  The head of IDF's Southern Command, Major General Matan 
Vilna'i, has called for improved coordination with the 
Palestinians and their future police force in the Strip. He was 
interview by Alan Ben-'Ami: 
  [Begin recording] [Vilna'i] The coordination now is very 
important, but one has to remember that they have to coordinate 
with us and not we are going to coordinate with them. I believe 
that it's good coordination with them. [passage omitted] 
  [Ben-'Ami] How long is it going to take you, from the time 
the agreement is signed, to actually complete the withdrawal? 
What do you estimate? 
  [Vilna'i] It depends on the treaty, on the exact treaty that 
we are going to sign with them. After we see the exact treaty, 
we'll decide what is the time that we need to withdraw. 
  [Ben-'Ami] Can you do it within a matter of hours? 
  [Vilna'i] We can do it from hours to several years. No 
problem. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

