<H3> <TI>   IDF Resumes Full Operation in Gaza Refugee Camps </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Resumes Full Operation in Gaza Refugee Camps </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1004111394 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 10 Apr 94 pp A1, A10 </F>
<F P=103> TA1004111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Eytan Rabin, Aluf Ben, and Shlomo Dror] </F>
  [Excerpt] IDF [Israel Defense Forces] troops in the Gaza 
Strip have in the last few days resumed full operation, mainly 
in the refugee camps and the big cities. The undercover units 
have also stepped up their operations in the wake of new 
instructions issued by senior Southern Command officers. 
  The Southern Command expects an increase in the attempts to 
perpetrate terror attacks due to the population's frustration as 
a result of the general closure of the territories and its close 
enforcement in the Gaza Strip. Consequently, it decided to step 
up the IDF's operations in the refugee camps and in the big 
cities. 
  Last Friday, IDF troops operated in the Dayr al-Balah 
refugee 
camp, arresting a Fatah wanted man suspected of murdering a 
70-year-old resident of Kefar Sava in February. [passage 
omitted] 
  [A report by Arye Kiesel and Shim'on Schiffer in Tel Aviv 
YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew on 10 April on pages 1 and 20 adds: 
"A considerable part of the IDF's regular combat forces is 
currently deployed in the territories to assure a maximum 
enforcement of the closure. 
  ["The training program of many units has been halted to 
enable their transfer to the territories. The troops 
meticulously monitor every road, passage, and footpath leading 
from the territories into Israel."] 

</TEXT>

