<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Four Iraqis Seek Asylum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Four Iraqis Seek Asylum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0804085694 Paris AFP in English 0704 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0804085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jerusalem, 8 April (AFP) -- Four Iraqis crossed the 
border from Jordan into northern Israel on Friday [8 April], 
sparking a major security alert, military officials said. 
  The Iraqis, who were unarmed, gave themselves up and asked 
for political asylum. 
  However when army spotters sighted the men just south of the 
Sea of Galilee the alert was sounded fearing an armed 
infiltration was underway. 
  Half a dozen cases of Iraqis, some army deserters, reaching 
the Israeli border with Jordan have been reported in the last 
two years. All have requested political asylum or to be allowed 
to travel on to a third country. 

</TEXT>

