<H3> <TI>   Beilin on Visit to Oman, Participation Parameters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beilin on Visit to Oman, Participation Parameters </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0604061894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0405 GMT 6 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0604061894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview with Deputy Foreign Minister Yosi </F>
Beilin by Karmit Gay; place not given -- live] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] 
  [Gay] Your trip to Oman seems less certain than before, 
since the hosts of the multilateral conference on water asked 
the Israelis to postpone their arrival. 
  [Beilin] It is true, such a request was presented. There 
had been a tendency, even a decision to send the preliminary 
group on 3 April, but they asked to put it off to 10 April. We 
do not know yet whether their demand reflects a desire to change 
the parameters of our participation. We will only know it when 
the preliminary delegation arrives there. If it transpires that 
they want to change the parameters -- namely, to limit our 
participation or deny media attendance, we will insist that the 
Oman encounter be identical to the other multilateral forums in 
every sense. We are definitely not going to agree to any change 
of the talks' parameters. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

