<H3> <TI>   Minister Harish Travels To Morocco for GATT Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Harish Travels To Morocco for GATT Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1004160594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 10 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1004160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Industry and Trade Minister Mikha Harish left for 
Morocco this afternoon to represent Israel in the final round of 
GATT talks. This agreement is supposed to lift trade 
restrictions and expand it by $300 billion per year. Israel can 
also benefit from this agreement. The conference will open in 
Marrakech tomorrow. It will be attended by representatives of 
114 countries. Minister Harish told our correspondent Arye 
Schorr he hopes to use the conference for holding contacts with 
representatives of Arab countries that do not have relations 
with Israel. 

