<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Papal Nuncio Announces Pope Postpones Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Papal Nuncio Announces Pope Postpones Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1104111194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 11 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1104111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Speculation among political, spiritual, and 
media circles that the pope's visit to Lebanon would be 
postponed was confirmed today when two statements were issued, 
one by the Vatican and the other at a news conference held by 
Papal Nuncio Pablo Puente in the Vatican Embassy in Harisa at 
noon today. Puente, who returned to Beirut yesterday following 
a brief visit to the Vatican, officially announced that Pope 
John Paul II's visit to Lebanon has been postponed until a date 
to be decided, when conditions are more suited to such a visit 
producing the expected results. [passage omitted] 
  In the first reaction to the postponement of the visit, 
Shaykh Muhammad Mahdi Shams-al-Din, chairman of the Higher 
Islamic Shiite Council, received a message from Papal Nuncio 
Pablo Puente informing him of the postponement of the pope's 
visit to Lebanon. His eminence expressed his regret over the 
postponement of the visit, which had been awaited by Lebanon and 
the Lebanese in view of the pope's position in the hearts of all 
the Lebanese. His eminence added: We hope the circumstances 
will become suitable for the pope to make his visit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

