<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<H3> <TI>   GCC Trade Ministers Open Trade Committee Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    GCC Trade Ministers Open Trade Committee Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604182994 Riyadh SPA in Arabic 1700 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0604182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Riyadh, 6 Apr (SPA) -- Their excellencies the 
ministers of trade in the Gulf Cooperation Council [GCC] states 
began the proceedings of the 20th session of the Trade 
Cooperation Committee at the GCC headquarters in Riyadh today. 
  Dr. Sulayman al-Salim, Saudi commerce minister and chairman 
of the current session, delivered a speech at the start of the 
meeting, welcoming the GCC trade ministers and hailing the depth 
of cooperation between the GCC states. [passage omitted] 
  His excellency concluded his speech by saying: 
"International 
changes are aimed at achieving real free trade, particularly now 
that all the difficulties have been overcome and the Uruguay 
Round has ended in success. Endeavors are also under way to 
turn GATT into an international trade organization at the 
meeting due to be held in Marrakesh soon. All this imposes 
challenges on us and obliges us to make huge efforts to achieve 
greater freedom of trade among us; we must remove all procedural 
obstacles in order to pave the way so that we may keep up with 
and adapt to these positive international trends." 
  He also said that he hoped that everyone would cooperate to 
take more national goods off the list of the goods on which 
there is an import ban. He added that he would like to see the 
competent authorities reach a suitable formula to unify tariffs 
within the GCC. After this the commerce minister announced the 
end of the opening session. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

