<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Resigns Prior to Reshuffle </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Resigns Prior to Reshuffle </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0904140994 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1320 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0904140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuwait, 9 Apr -- 'Abd al-'Aziz al-Dakhil, minister 
of state for cabinet affairs, has announced that the members of 
the Kuwaiti Government today tendered their resignations to the 
heir apparent and prime minister so as to carry out the required 
government reshuffle. 
  The minister of state for cabinet affairs told KUNA that a 
meeting was held today in the presence of all the ministers, 
during which the ministers studied the comprehensive speech that 
was delivered by the heir apparent and the prime minister to the 
Kuwaiti people last Monday [4 April], particularly the paragraph 
pertaining to the need for a government reshuffle in harmony 
with the requirements of the coming phase. 
  Al-Dakhil announced that the ministers agreed to give the 
heir apparent an opportunity to carry out the required 
reshuffle. To this end, all the ministers then submitted their 
resignations to the heir apparent and prime minister, who is 
expected to take the necessary measures in this regard. 
  The minister of state for cabinet affairs added that all 
ministers will remain in their posts until the issuance of the 
appropriate decrees on the new government composition. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

